data.description: Join the BOLD Center at Douglass as we host our annual career conference! The Christiana Foglio DC'84 Douglass Career Conference is designed to empower students through career planning, discuss topics related to the workforce, and meet other professionals in a variety of industries to share their wealth of knowledge. Learn tips and tools for starting your career, how to navigate networking and interviewing, and the best ways to make your mark in the workplace. With a special focus on doing good work, we will also be hosting a packing party at the conference this year to donate items to community partners in need.  There will be food, giveaways, prizes, and networking opportunities.

data.organizationName: The BOLD Center at Douglass for Leadership, Career and Personal Development

data.description: Stop by Douglass Library to experience a solo exhibition of artwork by the 2025-2026 Lebowitz Artist-in-Residence, Liz Collins, on view September 2 through March 13! Collins is a Brooklyn based artist that works across art and design. She is known for her innovative multimedia fabric, knitwear, and textile work, along with the fashion label she created. Don't miss out—RSVP today and join the Center for Women in the Arts at Douglass to view the exhibition during a reception and for a talk by artist Liz Collins on October 16, from 5:00 to 6:30 PM! All are welcome!Schedule: 5:00-5:30pm exhibition viewing & reception (light refreshments served); 5:30-6:30pm artist’s talk. This experience counts towards the Douglass Discovery curriculum requirement.
